'''Ibrahim Adel Aly Mohamed Hassan''' ({{langx|ar|إِبْرَاهِيم عَادِل عَلِيّ مُحَمَّد حَسَن}}; born 23 April 2001), is an Egyptian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Nordsjælland]], on loan from [[UAE Pro League]] side [[Al Jazira Club|Al Jazira]] as a [[left winger]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ibrahim-adel/613135/ |title=Ibrahim Adel - Player profile |work=Soccerway |accessdate=18 May 2021}}</ref>

== Career ==
On 2 February 2026, [[Danish Superliga]] side [[FC Nordsjælland]] announced the signing of Adel on a loan-deal for the rest of the season, with an option to make it permanent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcn.dk/nyheder/2026/februar/ibrahim-adel-til-fcn|title=Ibrahim Adel til FCN|trans-title=Ibrahim Adel to FCN|publisher=FC Nordsjælland|language=da|date=2 February 2026}}</ref>
On 15 May 2026, the deal was made permanent, which him signing af contract until June 2029.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcn.dk/nyheder/2026/maj/ibrahim-adel-2029|title=FC Nordsjælland indfrier købsoption på Ibrahim Adel|trans-title=FC Nordsjælland exercises purchase option on Ibrahim Adel|publisher=FC Nordsjælland|language=da|date=15 May 2026}}</ref>

== International career ==

On 2 December 2025, Adel was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

